President Biden has declared a major disaster in South Carolina due to the effects of Hurricane Ian. Federal funding will be available to affected individuals and local governments in several counties for housing, repairs, and other recovery efforts. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) has named Kevin A. Wallace, Sr. as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Residents and business owners can apply for assistance through the FEMA website, phone, or app. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.